In geometry, an 'icosahedron' ( or ) is a regular polyhedron with 20 identical
equilateral triangular faces, 30 edges and 12 vertices. It is one of the five
Platonic solids.

It has five triangular faces meeting at each vertex. It can be represented by

{3,5}. It is the dual of the dodecahedron, which is represented by {5,3}, having
